    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "i get that, but i've heard some people say that those huge protests and the nonviolent stuff like MLK did were actually less effective than the more militant groups or the riots that happened. was the nonviolent approach actually the \"correct\" way to do things, or was that just the version that ended up in the history books?",
